  "prompt": "Has California ever voted for a Republican in the general election?",
  "response": "Yes, California has voted for a Republican candidate in the general election for president in the past. The state supported Republican candidates in several elections during the mid-20th century. Notably, Richard Nixon, who was born in California, won the state in both the 1968 and 1972 elections. Ronald Reagan, also a former governor of California, won the state in the 1980 and 1984 elections. However, since 1992, California has predominantly voted for Democratic candidates in presidential elections.",
